						<summary>

						<p>Base of the <hi rend="italic">dvārapāla</hi> image (right side) in the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This is an undated record and may be assigned to the 17th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the images of <hi rend="italic">dvārapālakas</hi> were caused to be made by Anumanabōyuḍu son of Nāgana bōyuḍu.</p>						

